data.description: Talk about backyard GOALS here at your new home at 12914 129th Terrace N in Largo Florida. This charming 3-bedroom, 2.5-bathroom home with a 2-car garage is nestled in a highly desired community in Largo just minutes from Indian Rocks Beach! With endless possibilities including a bonus bar space that can be converted to a 4th bedroom if desired!    As you enter, you'll be greeted by an open floor plan, with the living room, dining room, and kitchen adjoining to make entertaining easy. The master suite, includes an en-suite bathroom with a walk-in shower and a generous custom built walk-in closet.    The heart of this home is the incredible back bonus room, featuring vaulted ceilings that create an open and inviting atmosphere. The real showstopper here is the indoor bar area complete with a TV that will convey, perfect for entertaining guests. The bar is easily removable according to the seller if the new owner needs additional space.     The beautiful kitchen includes, stainless steel appliances, a wine fridge, and updated cabinetry and countertops that are unique to this home and designed specifically for those who enjoy an eclectic style!    Step outside, and you'll discover a complete oasis that feels like paradise with minimal maintenance required. The custom-built outdoor bar comes complete with a built-in grill and ice chest which is the perfect spot to host barbecues and gatherings all year long. The entertainment continues with an outdoor TV that will convey. Relax under the gazebo or on the large PVC decking, all recently installed, and enjoy the outdoor ambiance and the custom outdoor kitchen that the whole family will enjoy!    The backyard is designed for easy living, with artificial turf and crushed shells, ensuring that you have more time to enjoy your private retreat and less time on maintenance. Whether you're sipping cocktails at the outdoor bar, grilling up a feast, or simply unwinding in this serene space, you'll feel like you're on vacation every day.    To top it all off, this home is NOT part of a homeowners' association (HOA), and is NOT in a flood zone giving you super low monthly costs year around. Lots of homes in this area are vacation rentals, allowing it to be an investors dream! Don't miss this opportunity to own a piece of paradise just minutes from Indian Rocks Beach.
